[SN]TITLE[SN]
South Africa's anti-corruption campaigners deploy satire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
South Africa has found itself mired in some high-profile corruption scandals in recent years, causing the country to slip down the global transparency index.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
28 March 2016 Last updated at 16:50 BST
Now, campaigners have started using satire to shine a light on corrupt practices in the country.
The BBC's Lerato Mbele reports from Johannesburg.
